Description: Rim sherd of grey ware pottery trefoil oinochoe; dark grey fabric core, more light brown towards the edges, with mica inclusions; thick, very dark grey (almost black) slip on exterior; thin walled; thickened offset rim. Irregular rim and slight out-turn of neck, indicating that the piece belongs to part of the trefoil area of the neck.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.260, no.3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.151)
